The paper presents a framework for program induction that combines neural networks with probabilistic reasoning. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE). Among these, machine learning and artificial intelligence are the most likely sub-categories, as the paper focuses on the use of neural networks for program induction, which is a core topic in these fields. Natural language processing and computer vision are also relevant, as the paper evaluates the approach on a diagram question answering task, which involves both visual and textual inputs. Finally, neural networks is a relevant sub-category as the paper proposes a novel way of combining neural networks with probabilistic reasoning.
